				<td colspan="2"><span>Tremelo, are you the community correspondant?
<br />

<br />
I know there are some who are quite happy with the changes SoE have made, but I think, overall, there is a general disatisfation. What I have seen from your posts here, and on EQLive is to defend everything SoE is doing/have done. And I dont get it. I thought you were the community voice, and I thought the majority of posts that I have read have been unhappy about SOE, be it the new AA's, the new Songs or the way they have nerfed the Bard class again. I'm sure that you are there because you play the class very well, but are you representing the rest of the community? 
<br />

<br />
I'm not a lvl65 with xxx AA's, and I'm not someone who has AoE kited my way to 65 either (well, obvious really), but I did enjoy AE kiting (as well as the other forms of soloing at our disposal). I do agree that it was overpowered and something had to be done about it, but I, like many others I'm sure, do not think they changed it for the good of the class.
<br />

<br />
I'm not going to comment on the AA's and songs, as I have not reached that level, but its disheartning to see so many people complaining about all these things, yet you seem to approve. 
<br />

<br />
I'm not flaming you Tremelo, as I have alot of respect for someone who is put into a position such as this, but I do have to query some of your responses, which always seem to be the opposite of what I'm reading elsewhere?
<br />

<br />
Do I misunderstand the position you hold as Community Rep?
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
