<br />

<br />
Its very easy to judge when alot of the work you have done/are doing is not public but private and I can understand that position.
<br />

<br />
One major concern I do have though, is that SoE seem to have time to give us all the sparkle (shadows, reflective water etc) and nerfs, but not give us the fixes that the communtiy has asked for. Now, you could argue that Shadows and reflective water were part of Oow, but they were not. I'm going to assume that it took a developer x amount of hours to make these things possible. I think the communtiy as a whole, would rather have seen the class issues fixed, or at least attemt something, than have the extra sparkle. The sparkle does not give us anything to gameplay. Just makes it look nicer (although I have switched these options off after 10 mins and I would think many others too). This concern is not just for Bards, but every class that has outstanding issues.
<br />

<br />

<br />
