				<td colspan="2"><span>I too will not buy OOW until the dust settles - if even then.  GoD was a waste of money for me and I expect OOW will be as well.  I dont pretend to judge the quality of the roll out, the interesting zones or anything else about the expansion.  From what I understand about it, there is nothing there for me at this time.
<br />

<br />
I do believe that the AOE changes were wrong - not because I AOE, I dont, but because the change that was made was made for ease of programming not for better game play.
<br />

<br />
Yes it is not right that someone can kill 50+ mobs at once but looking at the gain only looks at one side of the issue and you can use the &quot;that is not right&quot; arguement for any power that a player has.  The correct way to address it was to fix the issues that enabled the exploit: the terrain and autocircle.  These are not easy to fix, I admit, but they are things that should have been fixed.  Heck, make all of LoY a selos free zone and the problem would go away.   
<br />

<br />
I also believe that the fix was rushed because of the OOW release - which means that the release went well at the expence of overall game play.  Again, I am not advocating AoE kiting but advocating the correct fix to the problem.
<br />

